Package com.example.app.models

Class Application

java.lang.Object
com.example.app.models.Application
All Implemented Interfaces:
BaseEntity
public class Application extends Object implements BaseEntity
Application class that represents an application made by a user for a project. It implements the BaseEntity interface. Provides methods to get and set application details.

    • Application

      public Application(Integer id, Integer userId, Integer projectId, ApplicationStatus status, Boolean requestWithdrawal, FlatType flatType)
      Constructor for the Application class with parameters.
      Parameters:
      id - the ID of the application. This field should be null for new applications. After saving to the database, it will be set.
      userId - the ID of the user who made the application
      projectId - the ID of the project for which the application is made
      status - the status of the application
      requestWithdrawal - indicates whether the user has requested to withdraw the application
      flatType - the type of flat the user is applying for
